      "span_text": "Moreover, our previous studies indicate that a higher ionic strength mainly slows down the adsorption without greatly influencing its mechanism, protein orientation on the surface or list of important interacting residues. During the simulations, the ionic distribution rapidly equilibrates and the charged surface is screened by the Na + ions, so that far above the surface there is no time-averaged electric field."
